
If you've already committed node_modules, you need to remove it from Git's tracking (but keep it locally):

bash
git rm -r --cached node_modules
git commit -m "Stop tracking node_modules"
Re-run the elocuent command if needed – the CSV file will still be generated, but Git will ignore the node_modules folder.

Your .gitignore can also include other common files (e.g., .DS_Store, *.log), but at minimum add node_modules/.

node_modules/
